.TH LIBRESCC 1 "2026" "librescc 1.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
librescc \- MIDI to SCC-inspired chiptune player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B librescc
[\fIFILE.mid\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
LibreSCC is a desktop application that converts Standard MIDI Files into
real-time synthesized chiptune audio, in the style of Konami's SCC sound
chip. It parses MIDI internally (no external playback tools), renders
audio in real time through PortAudio using a wavetable synth engine with
square, triangle, sine, and noise voices, ADSR envelopes, per-voice
low-pass filtering, and priority-based voice stealing across up to 32
configurable voices, shown as a two-row, 16-channel-per-row matrix with
a mute toggle on every channel.
.SH USAGE
Launch LibreSCC and either pass a MIDI file as an argument or drag-and-drop
a
.B .mid
file onto the window (the header bar's Open button also has an Open
Recent submenu). Use the Play/Stop buttons to control playback, the
polyphony slider to change the voice limit, the per-channel mute
toggles to silence individual channels instantly, the Config dialog to
switch between waveform presets, and the Export WAV / Export MP3
buttons to render the currently loaded file to an audio file. MP3
export requires LibreSCC to have been built with libmp3lame available;
otherwise the button is disabled.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I FILE.mid
Optional path to a MIDI file to load on startup.
.SH AUTHOR
LibreSCC contributors.
